description: Composite numbers n such that juxtaposition of prime factors of n has length 9.
comments: The last term is a(84018465) = 997210243 = 9973 * 99991. - _Giovanni Resta_, Mar 21 2013
links: Nathaniel Johnston, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
maple: isA036333 := proc(n) local d: d:=ifactors(n)[2]: return `if`(not isprime(n) and add(length(d[j][1])*d[j][2], j=1..nops(d))=9, n, NULL): end: seq(isA036333(n),n=2..5440); # Nathaniel Johnston, Jun 22 2011
author: _Patrick De Geest_, Dec 15 1998.
